{"id":"customer-support-mhw","title":"Beads-Tasklets Integration: API Key Authentication","description":"## Overview\nBidirectional sync between Tasklets tickets and beads issues. Auto-sync on session start + on-demand command.\n\n## Decisions Made\n\n| Question | Decision |\n|----------|----------|\n| API key scope | Tenant-wide |\n| Auto-create issues | Yes |\n| Priority system | P0-P4 (direct mapping) |\n| Sync trigger | Both: session start + on-demand |\n| Duplicate prevention | Store beads_issue_id in ticket |\n| Two-way sync | Yes - push/pull status, plans, notes |\n| Type mapping | All tickets → bug (can promote to feature/epic) |\n\n## Data Model Changes\n\n### Tickets table - add columns:\n- `beads_issue_id` - Link to beads issue (prevents duplicates)\n- `priority` - Change from 1-5 to P0-P4 enum\n\n### New api_keys table:\n- id, tenant_id, key_hash, name, is_active, created_at, last_used_at\n\n## Two-Way Sync Flow\n\n```\nPULL (Tasklets → Beads):\n- New ticket → bd create --type=bug\n- Ticket status change → bd update \u003cid\u003e --status=X\n- Ticket priority change → bd update \u003cid\u003e --priority=X\n\nPUSH (Beads → Tasklets):\n- Issue status change → PATCH /api/external/tickets/:id\n- Issue linked to epic/feature → update ticket metadata\n- Bug promoted to feature → update ticket category\n```\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n### External API (API key auth):\n- `GET /api/external/tickets` - List tickets (with filters)\n- `GET /api/external/tickets/:id` - Get single ticket\n- `PATCH /api/external/tickets/:id` - Update ticket (status, beads_issue_id, etc.)\n- `POST /api/external/tickets/:id/sync` - Trigger sync for specific ticket\n\n## Beads Integration\n\n### Hooks:\n- `session-start` - Pull new/updated tickets, create/update issues\n- Custom command: `bd sync-tickets` - Manual sync trigger\n\n### Issue metadata:\n- Description includes: `[Tasklets #123](http://localhost:4000/tickets/123)`\n- Labels/tags for epic/feature association\n\n## Files to Modify\n- `apps/api/src/db/schema.ts` - api_keys table, ticket.beads_issue_id, priority enum\n- `apps/api/src/middleware/apiKey.ts` - New API key auth middleware\n- `apps/api/src/routes/external.ts` - External API routes\n- `.beads/hooks/session-start.sh` - Sync hook\n- `scripts/bd-sync-tickets.sh` - On-demand sync command\n\n## Implementation Phases\n1. Schema: api_keys table + ticket columns\n2. API key middleware\n3. External API endpoints (CRUD)\n4. Beads hook (pull: Tasklets → Beads)\n5. Push sync (Beads → Tasklets)\n6. Testing \u0026 documentation","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-24T22:45:25.876064-05:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T09:54:48.054982-05:00"}
{"id":"customer-support-mz9","title":"Insights - Process Learnings \u0026 Experience Capture","description":"Capture learnings, hiccups, and wisdom as they happen during processes.\n\nInsight Types:\n- hiccup: Problem encountered, with solution\n- lesson: Key learning from experience\n- tip: Helpful shortcut or best practice\n- win: What went well, celebrate\n\nFields: process, customer, product, what_happened, root_cause, solution, next_time\n\nFilters: by process, customer, type, product, contributor\n\nFuture: Auto-generate runbooks from accumulated insights.\n\nTasklets Idea #9. Same pattern as Ideas/Prompts.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-25T09:51:10.332493-05:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T09:54:21.828455-05:00"}
